==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jougs
<hw>Jougs</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>joug</ets> a
yoke, L. <ets>jugum</ets>. See <er>Yoke</er>.]</ety> <def>An iron collar
fastened to a wall or post, formerly used in Scotland as a kind of
pillory. <altsp>[Written also <asp>juggs</asp>.]</altsp> See
<er>Juke</er>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jouissance</ent>⟦br⟧
